      "author_association" : "MEMBER",
      "body" : "Good point. So, `-netinfo` uses the version returned by `getnetworkinfo` for the version check\r\n\r\n```cpp\r\n        const UniValue& networkinfo{batch[ID_NETWORKINFO][\"result\"]};\r\n        if (networkinfo[\"version\"].get_int() < 209900) {\r\n            throw std::runtime_error(\"-netinfo requires bitcoind server to be running v0.21.0 and up\");\r\n        }\r\n```\r\n\r\nam now building 22.0rc3 from source ATM to look at updating the `-netinfo` header to return both client and server versions (maybe it doesn't work, am looking; it's an opportunity to re-verify that the server check functions as intended)\r\n```diff\r\n-        std::string result{strprintf(\"%s %s%s - %i%s\\n\\n\", PACKAGE_NAME, FormatFullVersion(), ChainToString(), networkinfo[\"protocolversion\"].get_int(), networkinfo[\"subversion\"].get_str())};\r\n+        std::string result{strprintf(\"%s %s%s - %i%s\\n\\n\", PACKAGE_NAME, networkinfo[\"version\"].get_int(), ChainToString(), networkinfo[\"protocolversion\"].get_int(), networkinfo[\"subversion\"].get_str())};\r\n```\r\n",
